In [3]:
function sir(beta,gamma,N,S0,I0,R0,tf)
    t = 0
    S = S0
    I = I0
    R = R0
    ta=[]
    Sa=[]
    Ia=[]
    Ra=[]
    while t < tf
        push!(ta,t)
        push!(Sa,S)
        push!(Ia,I)
        push!(Ra,R)
        pf1 = beta*S*I
        pf2 = gamma*I
        pf = pf1+pf2
        dt = rand(Exponential(1/pf))
        t = t+dt
        if t>tf
            break
        end
        ru = rand()
        if ru<(pf1/pf)
            S=S-1
            I=I+1
        else
            I=I-1
            R=R+1
        end
    end
    results = DataFrame()
    results[!,:t] = ta
    results[!,:S] = Sa
    results[!,:I] = Ia
    results[!,:R] = Ra
    return(results)
end

function HILL(x,n,K,α)
    return (α*x^n/(K+x^n))
end
Out[25]:
HILL (generic function with 1 method)
In [26]:
function gillespie1(A0,B0,i0,j0,k0)
    t=0
    V=1e3
    tf=1e5
    i=i0
    j=j0
    k=k0
    rates=[]
    K_rate=1
    ta=[]
    ia=[]
    ja=[]
    ka=[]
    while t<tf
        push!(ta,t)
        push!(ia,i)
        push!(ja,j)
        push!(ka,k)
        N=i+j+k
        α=50
        #println(N)
        k1=K_rate*A0*B0*HILL(i,1,1,α)
        k2=K_rate*A0*B0*HILL(i,1,1,α)
        k3=0
        k_a=[k1,k2,k3]
        K_sum=k1+k2+k3
        #dt = rand(Exponential(1/K_sum))
        dt=(1.0/K_sum)*log(1/rand())
        t = t+dt
        if t>=tf || N>=V
            println(t,"\t",N,"\t","Stop")
            break
        end
        ru = rand()
        if ru<(k1/K_sum)
            j=j+1    
        elseif ru>(k1/K_sum) && ru<((k1+k2)/K_sum)
            k=k+1
        else
            i=i+1
        end
    end
    results = DataFrame()
    results[!,:t] = ta
    results[!,:i] = ia
    results[!,:j] = ja
    results[!,:k] = ka
    return (results)
end

In [205]:
function get_rates(Adj,Pop_vec,A0,B0)
    N_reactions=sum(Adj)  #Each A_ij=1 stands for a reaction
    rates=[]
    α=1e3
    K_rate=1.0
    indices=findnz(sparse(Adj))  # if adj[i,j]==1 then set of i's are indices[0] and set of j's are indices[1]
   # println(indices)
    z=zip(indices[1],indices[2]) # zip the sets
    #println(z)
    rates=zeros(Float64,length(Adj[1,:]))
    #rates=fill(K_rate*A0*B0,length(Adj[1,:]))
    rates=fill(0.0,length(Adj[1,:]))
    for inds ∈ z
        #println(inds[1],"\t",inds[2],"\t",rates[Int(inds[1])])
        rates[Int(inds[1])] = rates[Int(inds[1])]+K_rate*A0*B0*HILL(Pop_vec[ inds[2] ],1,1,α)
    end
    prob=[]
    append!(prob,0)
    for j in 1:length(rates)
        append!(prob,sum(rates[1:j])/sum(rates))
    end
    data=Dict(
            ":rates" => rates,
            ":prob" => prob
    )
    return data
end

function Gillespie_step(Adj,pop_vec,A0,B0)
    data=get_rates(Adj,pop_vec,A0,B0)
    dt=(1.0/sum(data[":prob"]))*log(1/rand())
    zu=rand()
    #println(data[":prob"])
    reaction=searchsortedfirst(data[":prob"], zu)-1
    #println(reaction)
    pop_vec[reaction]=pop_vec[reaction]+1
    return(dt,pop_vec)
end

function Gillespie(Adj,A0,B0,init_pop)
    t=0
    V=500
    tf=200
    pop_vec=init_pop
    P=Dict()
    for i in 1:length(Adj[1,:])
        P[string(Int(i))]=[]
    end
    P["t"]=[]
    while t<=tf
        for j in 1:length(pop_vec)
            append!(P[string(Int(j))],pop_vec[j])
        end
        append!(P["t"],t)
        N=sum(pop_vec)
        dt,pop_vec=Gillespie_step(Adj,pop_vec,A0,B0)
        t=t+dt
        println(N)
        if N>=V
            break
        end
    end
    return(P)
end
